D. On ξ 75, lectuli Punicani.

The received interpretation of this passage is, that part of Tubero's bad taste was shewn in providing mean couches for the guests to recline upon at the banquet. I wish to trace up the authorities for this view and against it.

1. Valerius Maximus V11 5 tells the same story, almost word for word after Cicero 3 but in pointing out the offence given to the Roman people, he says not a word about the lectuli as mean, or as having been in any way improper3 on the contrary, he says that the people punished the public scandal of such an entertainment by voting against Tubero at the praetorian election, because it thought non unius convivii numerum sed totam se in illis pelliculis iacuisse, thus laying the whole stress on the skins.
